title: US & Russia's Secret Ukraine Plan, AI's Music Industry Takeover, Mary Fowler's New Book | 10 News+
description: Beloved Matildas superstar Mary Fowler has made a bombshell claim in her new book ‘Bloom: Creating A Life I Love’, alleging she faced racism when playing for the French club Montpellier HSC. Fowler describes an instance where she and another player, who is Black, were handed bananas as gifts, while other teammates received flowers.  Sussan Ley has defended the Liberal Party’s track record on net zero, immigration, and defence policy. She insists her party is united, and that criticism of her shift towards the political right is only coming from the Canberra bubble. It comes as more turmoil continues within the Liberals, with Mark Speakman handing in his shock resignation as New South Wales’ Opposition Leader.  Australian musicians are concerned over a global surge in AI-produced tracks. At this year’s Golden Guitars, judges suspected four tracks to be completely AI-generated, and issued a blanket ban on the technology. Industry experts hope the fight against artificial intelligence will be led by committed artists and their fans, who want to create and listen to real music.  Ryan Wedding, a former Olympic snowboarder from Canada, has been added to the FBI’s 10 most wanted list. Authorities are offering up to US$15 million for information leading to his arrest. Wedding is accused of running an transnational drug trafficking operation, and the charges are connected to his alleged involvement in the killing of a witness who was about to testify in a US federal court.
